<div id="questionHelpModel" class="modal modal-fixed-footer">
    <div class="modal-content">
        <h4>Question</h4>
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-12 openlap-help">
                <p >here the user formulates the core question which he or she wants to get answered. E.g. a simple LA question can be "How active are students in my courseroom?". To answer this question, the user define a set of indicators and associate them with the question. Following are the three ways how a user can create indicator.</p>

                <p ><a class="btn-floating light-blue darken-2"><i class="material-icons">add</i></a> <b>Define new:</b> Using this the user can define a new indicator from scratch by defining dataset, applying filter, analyzing and visualizing. More details in the indicator definition section.</p>

                <p ><a class="btn-floating yellow darken-1"><i class="material-icons">file_download</i></a> <b>Load Existing:</b> User can load an exting indicator created by someone else and modify it according to his or her needs.</p>

                <p ><a class="btn-floating red"><i class="material-icons">view_quilt</i></a> <b>Composite:</b> The indicators associated with the current LA question can be combined together to form a composite indicator. Only the indicator which applies the same analysis can be combined together. The composite indicator cannot be loaded for editing. More details in the composite indicator definition section.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="modal-footer">
        <button class="modal-close waves-effect waves-light btn light-blue darken-2" title="Close the dialog box." >
            Close
        </button>
    </div>
</div>